# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620037> (tile drain removal process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620037> "A mechanical hydrological alteration process in which a human uncovers and removes subterranean tile drains to reduce drainage on the landscape and restore wetland hydroperiod."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620037> "This term has been merged into tile drain decommissioning process (ELMO:3620036). See that term for the consolidated definition."@en)
