AnnotationAssertion(Annotation(<http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasDbXref> <doi:10.1016/j.ecoleng.2014.03.051>) <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620631> "A plant material transfer process in which a human collects material from the moss layer (approximately the top 10 cm) of a donor peatland and transfers it to a restoration site to reintroduce peatland-forming mosses and associated species."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3620631> "Hydrological restoration steps (e.g. blocking drainage ditches) that may precede or accompany moss transfer should be represented as separate processes under mechanical hydrological alteration process."@en)
