AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621027> "A chemical application process in which a human applies an acidifying amendment such as elemental sulfur to soil or water in order to lower the pH and improve conditions for acid-tolerant species such as heathland or bog vegetation."@en)
