# Class: <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621029> (hay transfer process)

AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000115> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621029> "A plant material transfer process in which a human cuts hay from a species-rich donor site and spreads it on a receptor restoration site in order to introduce plant propagules and associated invertebrates."@en)
AnnotationAssertion(<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000116> <https://w3id.org/elmo/elmo_3621029> "Added following Delphi survey recommendations."@en)
